[
    {
        "content": "<p><code>List.splitAt</code>, nee <code>List.split</code>, returns a record: <code>{before : List elem, others : List elem}</code>.  While before and others are adequate names, they may not always sum up what the split means to the rest of the program:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Elm\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"p\">{</span><span class=\"nv\">before</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">others</span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">splitAt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">vampireCombatSequence</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">666</span>\n<span class=\"err\">#</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">vs</span>\n<span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"nv\">preStakingEvents</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">postStakingEvents</span><span class=\"p\">)</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nf\">=</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"nf\">.</span><span class=\"nv\">splitAt</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"nv\">vampireCombatSequence</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"mi\">666</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Plus a tuple might be less surprising to someone coming from another functional language.</p>",
        "id": 448333589,
        "sender_full_name": "Francois Green",
        "timestamp": 1719841169
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>One point in favor of the records is that they make it (sort of) clear what is being returned; we have functions that return {before, others} and those that return {before, after}. Clarity can help prevent bugs.</p>",
        "id": 448337781,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton",
        "timestamp": 1719841904
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Presumably with this change, we would make it all the same for <code>List.splitAt, List.splitFirst, List.splitLast, Str.splitFirst and Str.splitLast</code></p>",
        "id": 448339079,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton",
        "timestamp": 1719842098
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>A point in favor of tuples would be cleaner type signatures:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Haskell\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nf\">splitLast</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">elem</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">elem</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"ow\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Result</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">(</span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">elem</span><span class=\"p\">,</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">elem</span><span class=\"p\">)</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"kt\">NotFound</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kr\">where</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">elem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">implements</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Eq</span>\n</code></pre></div>\n<p>Instead of:</p>\n<div class=\"codehilite\" data-code-language=\"Haskell\"><pre><span></span><code><span class=\"nf\">splitLast</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">:</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">elem</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"n\">elem</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"ow\">-&gt;</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Result</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">{</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">before</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">elem</span><span class=\"p\">,</span>\n<span class=\"w\">            </span><span class=\"n\">after</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">:</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">List</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">elem</span>\n<span class=\"w\">        </span><span class=\"p\">}</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"p\">[</span><span class=\"kt\">NotFound</span><span class=\"p\">]</span>\n<span class=\"w\">    </span><span class=\"kr\">where</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">elem</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"n\">implements</span><span class=\"w\"> </span><span class=\"kt\">Eq</span>\n</code></pre></div>",
        "id": 448340242,
        "sender_full_name": "Anton",
        "timestamp": 1719842246
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think they should all be tuples. They were just created before tuples</p>",
